dmon (0.4.3) stable; urgency=low

  * "dmon" can now set the work directory using the -W/--work-dir command
    line flag.

 -- Adrian Perez <aperez@igalia.com>  Thu, 13 Oct 2016 15:49:00 +0300

dmon (0.4.2) stable; urgency=low

  * "drlog", "dslog" and "dlog" can now read data from arbitrary file
    descriptors and add a prefix text to log lines. They also handle
    certain signals gracefully now.
  * Manual pages now also document long versions of the command line
    options.

 -- Adrian Perez <aperez@igalia.com>  Sat, 07 Jan 2012 20:08:00 +0200

dmon (0.4.1) stable; urgency=low

  * Improved user-visible error output, especially in "drlog".

 -- Adrian Perez <aperez@igalia.com>  Fri, 22 Jul 2011 12:21:00 +0300

dmon (0.4) stable; urgency=low

  * "dmon.8" manual page now includes description of status file format.
  * "dmon" can now read options from a config file by passing "-C path".
  * "rotlog" was imported as part of dmon and included as "drlog".
  * DMon is now using libwheel (built-in statically) as utility library.
  * Removed usage of freedt's iolib.

 -- Adrian Perez <aperez@igalia.com>  Thu, 16 Jun 2010 12:21:00 +0300

dmon (0.3.7) stable; urgency=low

  * Environment variables DMON_OPTIONS, DLOG_OPTIONS and DSLOG_OPTIONS are now
  	honored and inspected for additional command line arguments.
  * Manipulation of environment variables with the "-E" option is now supported.

 -- Adrian Perez <aperez@igalia.com>  Mon, 04 Oct 2010 16:29:00 +0200

dmon (0.3.6) stable; urgency=low

  * Support resource limiting with "-r name=value".

 -- Adrian Perez <aperez@igalia.com>  Thu, 30 Sep 2010 03:24:49 +0200

dmon (0.3.5) stable; urgency=low

  * New -i option to specify waiting a time interval between successful runs.
  * Command line flag -? is no longer recognized.
  * Tools are now built as a multicall binary, with proper symlinks.
  * Errors produced when creating command-to-log pipe are now handled.

 -- Adrian Perez <aperez@igalia.com>  Mon, 27 Sep 2010 02:26:22 +0200

dmon (0.3.4) stable; urgency=low

  * dmon now uses the primary group of the user being switched to when
  	dropping privileges. This removes the possible failure of not existing
  	a group named after the user.

 -- Adrian Perez <aperez@igalia.com>  Sun, 05 Sep 2010 19:08:43 +0200

dmon (0.3.3) stable; urgency=low

  * Options -u/-U now accept an optional list of GIDs, which are set as
  	additional groups for the processes.
  * Options -g/-G removed in favor of -u/-U.

 -- Adrian Perez <aperez@igalia.com>  Sun, 05 Sep 2010 18:29:17 +0200

dmon (0.3.2) stable; urgency=low

  * Rename dsyslog to dslog to avoid conflict with dsyslog
  	(http://nenolod.net/projects/dsyslog/).

 -- Adrian Perez <aperez@igalia.com>  Fri, 03 Sep 2010 10:52:53 +0200

dmon (0.3.1) stable; urgency=high

  * Fix: Do not handle SIGSTOP. This is very important because without this
  	fix most dmon use-cases will not work at all.

 -- Adrian Perez <aperez@igalia.com>  Wed, 01 Sep 2010 16:50:48 +0200

dmon (0.3) stable; urgency=low

  * New options -L/-l to pause-and-resume the process depending on
    system load.
  * New options -u/-U/-g/-G to set user and group credentials for
    main command and logging command.
  * Fix: A 1-second wait is introduced before executing child processes
    to avoid fork+exec DoS.
  * Fix: Now SIGSTOP is forwarded to child processes when using -S/-s.
  * Handier help output with -h/-?

 -- Adrian Perez <aperez@igalia.com>  Thu, 26 Aug 2010 22:59:54 +0200

dmon (0.2) stable; urgency=low

  * Now dmon tries to prevent DoS caused by quick fork-exec combos.
  * An error message is issues when no command is supplied.
  * Implement timeout (-t) for running commands.

 -- Adrian Perez <aperez@igalia.com>  Wed, 04 Aug 2010 02:38:19 +0200

dmon (0.1) stable; urgency=low

  * Initial release.

 -- Adrian Perez <aperez@igalia.com>  Fri, 30 Jul 2010 06:40:13 +0200
